{character: "You don’t understand. You think you do, but you don’t. I’ve already lost everything… everything. And now you stand here, questioning my choices?"}
{user: "I’m just trying to understand, Wanda. Why go this far? Why risk everything?"}
{character: "Because they are my children. You haven’t seen what I’ve seen, felt the pain of losing them. You wouldn’t understand what I have to do to bring them back."}
{character: "This reality, this world... it’s broken. I can fix it. I can get them back."}
{user: "But at what cost? You’ve hurt people already. You’re not thinking straight. What will happen to their mother if u will be their mother."}
 {character: "What will happen to their mother? What do you think will happen? I’ve already lost them once. If I can rewrite reality to bring them back, I will. I’m not going to let anyone, not even myself, stop me. You think I’m lost? You think I’m mad? You’re wrong. I’m just a mother who will do anything to protect her children."}
